<subSubSection id="C374652CFFC7FFACD4CCFB650993FAEA" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFC7FFACD4CCFB650993FAEA" blockId="58.[151,1437,942,2013]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC7FFACD4CCFB650C1AFB7B" bold="true" box="[199,322,1230,1256]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFC7FFACD5BEFB640FD5FB7A" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[437,653,1231,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guacharos" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC7FFACD5BEFB640FD5FB7A" box="[437,653,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Tenedos guacharos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC7FFACD69EFB640F8EFB7A" bold="true" box="[661,726,1231,1257]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFC7FFACD69EFB640F8EFB7A" box="[661,726,1231,1257]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFC7FFACD7A6FB640862FB7A" authority="Jocque &amp; Baert, 2002" authorityName="Jocque &amp; Baert" authorityYear="2002" box="[941,1338,1231,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peckorum">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC7FFACD7A6FB640960FB7A" box="[941,1080,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">T. peckorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFC7FFACD04BFB640862FB7A" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[1088,1338,1231,1257]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by having similar abdominal spots pattern; bifid median apophysis (MA), quadrangular-shaped, laminar anterior branch (aMA); complex retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B56FFC7FFACD73AFABC0936FAA2" author="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L." box="[817,1134,1303,1329]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="67 - 173" refId="ref79332" refString="Jocque, R. &amp; Baert, L. (2002) A revision of the Neotropical spider genera Tenedos O. P. - Cambridge and Ishania Chamberlin (Araneae, Zodariidae). Bulletin de l'Institut Royal des Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, Entomologie, 72, 67 - 173." type="journal article" year="2002">Jocqué &amp; Baert, 2002: 111</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 29A–B; figs 34C–F; 36A–D; 37A–B; 39C–F; 40C–D), but can be distinguished by having anterior branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis (aRTA) longer, apically sharp; sharp basal projection on base of embolus (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC7FFACD7DEFAF40906FAEA" box="[981,1118,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[158,1437,417,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-101@59.[151,1437,417,1740]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 39. Tenedos guacharos sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (IAvH-I-2972): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral view. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–D: 200µm; E–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520864/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Figs 39C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC7FFACD062FAF409E7FAEA" box="[1129,1215,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[282,1315,187,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-27@60.[271,1316,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 40. Tenedos mesa sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12336): A. Ventral view (arrow indicates the sclerotized process). B. Retrolateral view. Tenedos guacharos sp. n. C–D. Male palp (IAvH-I-2972): C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–D: 200µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; aRTA, anterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; BEP, basal embolar process; E, embolus; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; pMA, posterior branch of the median apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520868/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">40C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C374652CFFC7FFADD4CCFA290CC7FEF6" lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFC7FFADD4CCFA290F2CFED2" blockId="58.[151,1437,942,2013]" lastBlockId="59.[151,1437,151,393]" lastPageId="59" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC7FFACD4CCFA290C01FA0F" bold="true" box="[199,345,1410,1436]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC7FFACD554FA280CC1FA0E" box="[351,409,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54D58805FFC7FFACD5ACFA280F4CFA0E" box="[423,532,1411,1437]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Holotype</typeStatus>
, IAvH-I-2972). Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC7FFACD747FA280E8EFA0E" box="[844,982,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[158,1437,417,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-101@59.[151,1437,417,1740]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 39. Tenedos guacharos sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (IAvH-I-2972): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral view. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–D: 200µm; E–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520864/files/figure.png" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Fig. 39A–B</figureCitation>
): carapace brown-reddish slightly darker in margins. Chelicerae with paturon base dark brown, fangs brown-reddish. Endites light brown, white on anterior region. Labium and sternum brown. Legs: coxae I–IV light brown. Femora-tarsi I–IV brown with light spots. Abdomen: dorsally dark gray with five white guanine spots organized as follows: two small and rounded spots very close to each other, anteriorly positioned; two rounded spots and smaller than previous ones, medially positioned; one transversal and wide band, posteriorly positioned. Lateral and ventrally dark gray without spots. Measurements: total length 5.08, carapace length 2.78, width 1.65, height 1.22. Clypeus height 0.47. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.11, ALE 0.14, PME 0.12, PLE 0.14; AME–AME 0.19, AME–ALE 0.26, AME–PME 0.29, PME–PME 0.27, PME–PLE 0.27, ALE–PLE 0.28. Chelicerae 0.78 length. Sternum length 1.07, width 0.93. Legs: I—femur 1.72/ patella 0.58/ tibia 1.69/ metatarsus 1.62/ tarsus 1.13/ total 6.74; II—1.37/ 0.61/ 1.28/ 1.22/ 0.73/ 5.21; III—1.31/ 0.58/ 1.18/ 1.31/ 0.64/ 5.02; IV—1.71/ 0.85/ 1.37/ 2.05/ 0.86/ 6.84. Abdomen length 2.21. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): I—metatarsus v1r-1r-2; III—tibia v2-2-2, metatarsus v2-1p-2. Palp: retrolateral process of cymbium (RPC) long, widening towards base, external edge rounded; tegulum (T) large, rounded, longer than wide; subtegulum (St) small, longer than wide in ventral view, external edge small, rounded, rounded ventral projection; conductor (C) developed, wide, with large tubular basal projection; appendix (ApC) long, apically sharp; embolus (E) long, filiform towards apex; base of embolus (EB) approximately as long as three times basal tegular membrane; basal tegular membrane (BTM) originated proximally on tegulum, flattened, ending as very short appendix apically rounded; spermatic ducts (SD) S-shaped with both folds full open, thin; ventral tibial apophysis (VTA) small, short; median apophysis (MA) large, bifid, anterior branch (aMA) squared, laminar, posterior branch (pMA) tubular, short, wide at base; retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) very large, complex, consisting of anterior branch (aRTA) very thin, posterior branch (pRTA) wide without apical denticles, curved towards dorsal side (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC6FFADD575FE8C0F5FFED2" box="[382,519,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[158,1437,417,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-101@59.[151,1437,417,1740]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 39. Tenedos guacharos sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (IAvH-I-2972): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral view. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–D: 200µm; E–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520864" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520864/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Figs 39C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFC6FFADD619FE8C0F30FED2" box="[530,616,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1853,1877]" captionTargetBox="[282,1315,187,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-27@60.[271,1316,181,1829]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="FIGURE 40. Tenedos mesa sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12336): A. Ventral view (arrow indicates the sclerotized process). B. Retrolateral view. Tenedos guacharos sp. n. C–D. Male palp (IAvH-I-2972): C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–D: 200µm. Abbreviations: ApC, appendix of the conductor; aRTA, anterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; BEP, basal embolar process; E, embolus; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; pMA, posterior branch of the median apophysis; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520868/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">40C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFC6FFADD4CCFEE00CC7FEF6" blockId="59.[151,1437,151,393]" box="[199,415,331,357]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFC6FFADD4CCFEE00C7BFEF6" box="[199,291,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Female.</emphasis>
